SYNOPSIS
========
   int strstr(string str, string str2         )
   int strstr(string str, string str2, int pos)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Returns the index of str2(E) in str(E), searching from position pos(E) on.

   The returned index is relative to the beginning of the string. If str2(E) 
   is not found in str(E), -1 is returned.

   If pos(E) is negative, it designates the start position relative to the end
   of the string (the search will still proceed towards the end of the 
   string).

SEE ALSO
========
   strrstr(E), strlen(E), sscanf(E), sprintf(E), explode(E)
